.container#about
  h1 About
  p We're a free and open access scientific collaboration network.
  ul style="margin-left: 25px;"
    li Follow <a href="http://arxiv.org">arXiv.org</a> categories and see the highest ranked new papers
    li Scite papers and subscribe to categories
    li <a href="/signup">Sign up</a> to customize your view of the site

  p You can get in touch with us by emailing <a href="https://www.mit.edu/~aram/">Aram</a>.
    Or talk to us on our <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/scirate">mailing list</a>.

  p All user data is licensed under a
    <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/">Creative Commons
    license</a>. The code is also open source. This means that you can run your own
    version of SciRate for your research group or university. Visit
    <a href="http://github.com/scirate/scirate">GitHub</a>
    to view the source or to
    <a href="https://github.com/scirate/scirate/issues?state=open">report bugs</a>
    and request features. We welcome contributors!

  p We use arXiv's API to get the latest papers.
    Sometimes the API is not updated until several hours after the arXiv announcement, which also delays SciRate.
    If a paper's title, abstract, or author list is updated on arXiv, it may not be updated on SciRate.
    To report any data issues or request changes, please email <a href="https://kunalmarwaha.com/mail">Kunal</a>.

